# CAREFUL IF YOU WANT TO EDIT. YOU MUST USE iso8859-15!
#
# Here you can define the type of menu
# Enter with such syntax:
# Title;Type[;flags;...]
#
# Title should be in English. In the runtime it'll be translated automatically.
#
# You may use Wildcard in Title, but use it only if no other way is possible!
# Wildcard only works at end of the title, e.g.:
# True: "Titlename*" => it will search after title, which begins with "Titlename"
# Wrong: "Title*name" => it will search after title, which contains "Title*name"
#
# Following types are available:
# menunormal, menucentered, setupnormal, setupcentered, help, bouquets, image, music, video
#
# Following flags are available:
# ;imgnum      # The Numbers of Menuitem are shown as image
# ;uppercase   # The text of Menuitem are upper cased

